\sqrt{a}+\sqrt{b}=r
\sqrt{a} = \dfrac{r^2+a-b}{2r}
 {\sqrt{a}} + {\sqrt{b}}\in\mathbb{Q} \implies {\sqrt{ab}} \in\mathbb{Q} \implies {\sqrt{ab}} + b={\sqrt{b}}({\sqrt{a}} + {\sqrt{b}})\in\mathbb{Q} \implies {\sqrt{b}}\in\mathbb{Q}  
